<TEXT>
<P>
A cable car jolted to a stop to avoid a car while descending a hill, but there 
were no serious injuries, authorities said. Several passengers complained of 
minor pain after being knocked against poles and other inside parts of the 
cable car on Mason Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Three women passengers went to San Francisco General Hospital, where they were 
in stable condition while being observed for possible injuries, a nursing 
supervisor said. The incident occurred when a car made a left-hand turn in 
front of the cable car at Union Street, said Police Officer Emmett Hickson. 
Because the trolley was headed downhill, the gripman already had the brake on 
and was forced to apply the emergency brake to stop, Hickson said. 
