<P>
Meanwhile, Back at the Ranch: Michael Jackson led 82 children on a tour of his 
3,000-acre ranch outside Santa Barbara on Saturday and later served them lunch. 
Childhelp USA, a nonprofit organization for the prevention of child abuse, sent 
residents of its village for abused and neglected children near Beaumont, 
Calif., to Jackson's ranch, where he keeps giraffes, llamas and other exotic 
beasts. Jackson donated the proceeds from his last concert in Los Angeles to 
Childhelp after it renamed its research facility the Michael Jackson 
International Research Institute. CLAUDIA PUIG 
