<HEADLINE>
<P>
OIL SLICK THREATENING MOROCCO HEADS TO SEA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RABAT, Morocco 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Winds and currents are sweeping the remains of the oil slick that threatened 
Morocco's Atlantic coast out to sea, a government statement said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
It said the slick that once stretched 185 miles has now broken into two smaller 
sections, with the closest being 30 miles offshore. 
</P>
<P>
At one time, the 70,000-ton oil slick from the disabled Iranian supertanker 
Kharg 5 had drifted to within 10 miles of shore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
