<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA HABRA; 
</P>
<P>
DRIVER IN FATAL CRASH ALSO DIES OF INJURIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspected drunk driver died early Sunday a day after he allegedly ran a red 
light and rammed his car broadside into another car, killing one person and 
injuring three others, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
Jose Fragoso, 25, of Paramount died of his injuries about 1:15 a.m. at UCI 
Medical Center in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
He was admitted in critical condition Saturday with multiple fractures and head 
injuries. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred about 1:45 a.m. Saturday at the intersection of Beach 
Boulevard and Imperial Highway when Fragoso's car struck a vehicle driven by 
Marvin Olsen, 50, of Orange, who was hurt in the crash. 
</P>
<P>
Dead at the scene was Joseph Carillo, 34, of Long Beach, a passenger in 
Fragoso's car along with Mario M. Garcia, 36, who remains in critical condition 
at Mission Hospital Regional Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
Olsen and his passenger, Sherry Herring, 33, of Anaheim, were in stable 
condition Sunday at La Habra Community Hospital. Fragoso was arrested on 
suspicion of felony drunk driving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
