<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCI MAY LOSE 2 PLAYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELLIOTT TEAFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FRESNO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Guard Brett Pagett reportedly has left the UC Irvine basketball team to enroll 
at Rancho Santiago College, where his father, Dana, is the coach. 
</P>
<P>
Coach Bill Mulligan said, "It's up to him." Pagett, a sophomore from Los 
Alamitos High School, averaged 0.4 points a game last season, but has been 
sidelined by a foot injury. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Labat, a senior swingman, also might leave the team, Mulligan said. A 
reserve, Labat had the flu over Christmas vacation and did not practice with 
the team. He has lost 20 pounds, according to Mulligan. Labat and Mulligan will 
meet Wednesday to discuss the player's future. ELLIOTT TEAFORD 
</P>
</TEXT>
