LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
PARTY CRASHER SOUGHT IN SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspected gang member is being sought in a fatal shooting at a Lancaster 
birthday party, the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department said today. 
</P>
<P>
Christopher Sanford, 18, died at 9:30 a.m. Sunday at Antelope Valley Medical 
Center, about 10 hours after the Saturday night shooting at a home in the 44700 
block of Benald Street, Deputy Roger Hom said. 
</P>
<P>
A guest at the party, Sheldon Culver, 24, was hospitalized and in stable 
condition with a gunshot wound. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman, believed to be 16 to 18 years old, has not been identified, 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
Hom said the incident began when three suspected gang members attempted to 
crash a birthday party at the Benald Street home. There was a dispute as the 
three were being ejected and one of them drew a gun and shot Culver in the 
neck. 
</P>
<P>
The three were then chased from the house, Hom said. In front of the home, the 
gunman turned and fired a shot at his pursuers and instead shot Sanford, who 
had not been involved in the incident, Hom said. 
</P>
<P>
"He just happened to be leaving the party at that time," Hom said. 
</P>
<P>
Hom said the three teen-agers who crashed the party escaped. 
</P>
</TEXT>
