</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Visa International announced today that Czechoslovakia's oldest retail bank 
will begin offering Visa cards to citizens there next year. 
</P>
<P>
The Visa cards to be offered by Zivnostenska Banka will represent the first 
international payment card issued in Czechoslovakia. 
</P>
<P>
The bank intends to initially offer a regular Visa card and a Visa Business 
Card for frequent travelers to customers with income in foreign currency. 
</P>
<P>
The cards will access the customer's own funds, according to Visa 
International. 
</P>
<P>
"This not only marks a significant breakthrough to a new Eastern European 
market, it is a graphic illustration of the payment card as an international 
currency," Jean-Jacques Desbons, executive vice president of Visa 
International, said in a statement. 
