<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
KRONBERGER WINS GIANT SLALOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HINTERSTODER, Austria 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Petra Kronberger won her third World Cup race of the season today by capturing 
the women's giant slalom. 
</P>
<P>
The Austrian, second fastest after the first run, registered a total time of 2 
minutes 21.44 seconds for the win. 
</P>
<P>
Austrian Anita Wachter was second with an aggregate time of 2:21.95. Veronika 
Sarec of Yugoslavia, who had the second fastest overall time, was disqualified 
after losing a ski in the final stages. 
</P>
<P>
Michela Gerg of West Germany, who heads the standings with 148 points, was 
third in 2:22.94. Diann Roffe of the United States was sixth in 2:23.68. 
</P>
<P>
"It's all happened so quickly, it's difficult to believe," said Kronberger, who 
suddenly finds herself among the contenders in the World Cup standings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
